RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 1 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Claiming Purse 10800. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AIR KENNEY took over at the seven sixteenths pole and rated a slim lead over Long Cool through the backstretch, cleared that one midway on the turn and held well under steady handling. ROBBEDINTHEBAHAMAS chased outside through the backstretch, rounded the turn about the three path and finished well to take second the final yards. FLOOR IT chased through the backstretch, raced near the rail on the turn and was outfinished for second the final yards. LONG COOL engaged in close chase through the backstretch, but dropped back midway on the turn and flattened inside the eighth pole. SMOKIN SMITTY chased toward the inside, raced in the three path on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. FLASH OF DAY chased toward the inside, entered the turn at the rail, angled to the five path approaching the top of the lane and showed little further. MONEY MAC gave chase outside, raced in the five path on the turn and showed little in the lane.

ENTRY.NAME: Air Kenney
ENTRY.COMMENT: up 7/16,rated pace,urged clear mid turn,held well driving

ENTRY.NAME: Flash of Day
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,rail into turn,angled 5p near 1/8,little in lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 2 4 1/2F Dirt CR: 73. Claiming Purse 16600. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Three Races Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000, For Each $1,000 To $8,000 1 lb. (Races Where Entered For $6,25 0 Or Less Not Considered In Weight Allowances)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SNOWY JUBA CAT chased through the backstretch and raced close off the rail on the turn, dug in for the lead later yards and drew clear toward the wire. RIVER REWARDS RVF gave chase, raced in the three path on the turn and dug in to take second the final stride. SHUTUPN'KISSME took a quick lead and angled to the inside to set the pace, came under pressure leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the turn at the rail and dug in leaving the turn, but was caught late then nipped from second the final stride. CORA'S CHOICE gave chase, raced off the rail on the turn and ran evenly in the lane. GILDED QUEST chased through the backstretch, entered the turn off the rail, angled out nearing the head of the lane and ran evenly in the stretch. MY SISTER CLURRIE chased, raced in the four and five paths on the turn and showed little in the lane. CHURCH KEY gave chase inside and rounded the turn at the rail. LIME AFTER LIME saved ground.

ENTRY.NAME: Snowy Juba Cat
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased,close off rail turn,up late,clear near wire

ENTRY.NAME: Gilded Quest
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Ronney W and Richie Rich Racing Stable

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 3 1 1/16M Dirt CR: 89. Claiming Purse 13200. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE JUNE 13, 2023. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since June 13 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000, if for $4,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility)(W V A Races Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ICE BAR saved ground well back from early contention, started a bid into the backstretch and steadily progressed from there, circled rivals six wide on the far turn and dug in determinedly to take over the final yards. RRACE DAY WARRIOR settled off the rail early on, bid nearing the seven sixteenths pole and raced five wide on the far turn, dug in with the edge leaving the eighth pole but was outfinished in the final yards. POLAR WIND settled back in the four and five paths, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced in the three path on the far turn, eased out at the head of the lane and dug in to take third later yards. SUBJECT TO CHANGE settled off the pace in the four and five paths, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole and took the edge in the three path on the far turn, but flattened leaving the eighth pole. BLAMEITONTHEFUN stalked from the three path then took a slim lead nearing the half mile pole, dueled from the three eighths pole but was met while between horses midway on the far turn and weakened in the stretch. MR HOOVER stalked two deep then challenged toward the seven sixteenths pole, raced close at the rail on the far turn then weakened in the lane. BLUEMOON JUSTICE saved ground. ALWAYS FORGIVEN raced well back in the three and four paths and showed little response through the backstretch. MAKE WAY raced well back and was not a factor. HONOR THE FLEET rated a slim lead inside, was met nearing the half mile pole and gave chase, but faded toward the quarter pole.

ENTRY.NAME: Ice Bar
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,bid 1/2,steady gain,circled 6p turn,up final yards

ENTRY.NAME: Mr Hoover
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Ronney W and Truett Wilbur

ENTRY.NAME: Polar Wind
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled 4& 5p,bid near 3/8,3p far turn,up 3rd later yards

ENTRY.NAME: Subject to Change
ENTRY.OWNER: Devane William E and King Adam

ENTRY.NAME: Rrace Day Warrior
ENTRY.COMMENT: off rail,bid 7/16,5wd far turn,led past 1/8,outfinished late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 4 7F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. FOR ACCREDITED WEST VIRGINIA-BRED MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MOON FALL stalked off the rail then challenged leaving the seven sixteenths pole, contested even terms two deep on the far turn and dug in determinedly to edge clear later yards. CALLISTO'S BRIGADE stalked from the three path, took the lead three wide past the seven sixteenths pole, contested even terms at the rail on the far turn and dueled close through the upper stretch, but reluctantly ceded later yards. JUST MURPHY bobbled leaving the gate then saved ground, picked up the chase past the half mile pole, rounded the far turn about the three path, dug in from the head of the lane but flattened stride later yards. LORD CLANCY raced in the five path the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole and rounded the far turn about the four path, though, flattened in the lane. THEIRREGISTRDIMNOT settled in the three path the first turn, gave chase nearing the five sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn in the three and four paths and showed little further. JUBA'S MOCHA became anxious in the gate then saved ground, picked up the chase approaching the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and showed little in the lane. GAMBLING FEVER became anxious in the gate then took a quick lead and moved to the inside to show the way, was met leaving the seven sixteenths pole, gave chase from that point but dropped back toward the five sixteenths and weakened at the rail on the far turn. COLONIAL ROAD raced in the five path the first turn and never factored.

ENTRY.NAME: Juba's Mocha
ENTRY.COMMENT: anxious in gate,saved gorund,chased 3/8,off rail turn,weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Just Murphy
ENTRY.COMMENT: bobbled break,saved ground,chased 1/2,3p far turn,flattened late

ENTRY.NAME: Gambling Fever
ENTRY.OWNER: Brown Nicole and Brown Ronney W

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 5 7F Dirt CR: 76. Claiming Purse 17600. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of Three Races Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,000, allowed 2 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: MASTER THIS saved ground well off the early pace, bid approaching the three eighths pole, circled rivals in the six path on the far turn and dug in for the lead the final yards. SPRITZER took the lead and angled to the inside to show the way, came under pressure toward the five sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and dug in under steady encouragement through the lane, but was outfinished in the final yards. SUPERSTITIEUX was shuffled back shortly after the break and settled off the rail the first turn, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path then dueled through the stretch for third. SIR SMOAK settled in the three path the first turn, gave chase approaching the three eighths pole, raced in range of the lead in the three path on the far turn but flattened leaving the eighth pole. AKINGISALWAYSKING stalked from the five path the opening turn, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn in the five path and weakened in the lane. DAD'S LIL SPARK saved ground on the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn in the three path, eased out into the lane and showed little more. WINDSOR'S TRACKER stalked two deep the first turn, gave chase toward the seven sixteenths pole but weakened off the rail into the far turn. RIVER CROSROAD RVF stalked the earlier pace from the four path, picked up the chase nearing the three eighths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and weakened. MR CHANCE ROMANCE became a bit fractious in the gate then saved ground close to the early pace, gave chase past the half mile pole but weakened at the rail on the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Mr Chance Romance
ENTRY.COMMENT: bit fractious in gate,saved ground,chased 1/2,weakened rail turn

ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,bid near 3/8,circled 6p far turn,up final yards

ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,chased 3/8,3p far turn,eased out 1/8,empty lane

RACE.RACE_TEXT: CHARLES TOWN RACE 6 7F Dirt CR: 72. Maiden Special Weight Purse 26500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE, FOUR, FIVE, AND SIX YEARS OLD. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KEEN LOOKIN settled in the three path the first turn, bid leaving the three eighths pole and closed the gap in the four path on the far turn, took the nod past the eighth pole and dug in determinedly to inch clear toward the wire. TIME THE AVENGER rated close off the rail the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole and raced in range of the lead three wide on the far turn, dueled close to deep stretch but relented the final yards. FAST FORWARD rated a slim lead inside, dug in to the challenge of BATTLE BORN approaching the seven sixteenths pole, contested the edge at the rail on the far turn but was met past the eighth pole and flattened stride. The latter stalked two deep, challenged toward the seven sixteenths pole and contested even terms two deep on the far turn, then flattened the final sixteenth. RUM CUP saved ground on the first turn, picked up the chase toward the three eighths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn and showed little in the lane. AGAIN WE MEET saved ground well off the pace, showed little response through the backstretch, rounded the far turn near the rail and passed some rivals. RUN ROCKY RUN saved ground, picked up the chase leaving the three eighths pole, rounded the far turn at the rail and weakened. LET'S EAT was bumped leaving the gate then stalked from the three path, gave chase at the three eighths pole then gave way off the rail on the far turn. CHEATIN SONG broke outward and made contact with Let's Eat, rounded the first turn in the five path, gave chase past the seven sixteenths pole but weakened into the far turn.

ENTRY.NAME: Fast Forward
ENTRY.OWNER: Shive Charles Clark Patrick and Bright Derrick
ENTRY.COMMENT: rated slim lead,dug in 7/16,edge rail turn,met past 1/8,flattened

ENTRY.NAME: Cheatin Song
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke out,bumped break,5p 1st turn,chased 7/16,weakened into turn

ENTRY.NAME: Again We Meet
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,little response,rail far turn,passed rivals

ENTRY.NAME: Rum Cup
ENTRY.COMMENT: saved ground,chased near 3/8,off rail far turn,empty lane

CLAIM.OWNER: Eastham Richard and Brown Ronney W

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BAR FOURTEEN broke out and made contact with Golden Spoke then took a quick lead and rated the pace inside, came under pressure nearing the five sixteenths pole, contested even terms at the rail on the far turn and dug in determinedly to eke out the nod over the game stretch challenge of ZEN MASTER, who stalked from the three path the first turn and gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, dueled to even terms in the three path midway on the far turn and dug in gamely to the finish. KENNY HAD A NOTION stalked two deep then challenged leaving the seven sixteenths pole, but dropped back off the rail midway on the far turn and flattened in the lane. SUE LOVES BARBADOS was forced outward at the break then settled in the three path the first turn, picked up the chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the four path and showed little further. GOLDEN SPOKE was squeezed at the break then saved ground, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced off the rail on the far turn, eased outward entering the stretch and showed little more. TWO BIT KID rated close inside, gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, raced at the rail on the far turn and weakened into the lane. TREJO broke inward and made contact with Golden Spoke then dropped well back. MONSTER MASON ducked outward at the break, raced in the five path on the opening turn then gave chase leaving the seven sixteenths pole, though, showed little response.

ENTRY.NAME: Golden Spoke
ENTRY.OWNER: Pesaturo Gus and Joy Kevin J

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HONEYCAMP stalked off the rail the first turn, edged closer approaching the quarter pole and took the lead three wide past the pole, raced clear toward the head of the lane and was kept alert to widen the final sixteenth. SUPERSNAKE rated close inside, bid nearing leaving the seven sixteenths pole, eased outward midway on the far turn and left the turn about the five path, then dueled to clear second later yards. KATALIMA settled off the rail the first turn, gave chase from the seven sixteenths pole, rounded the far turn about the three path and came along to take third later yards. WINDSOR'S PLAY took the lead nearing the three quarter pole and moved to the inside to set the pace, was met approaching the seven sixteenths pole and dueled from that point, but dropped back at the rail midway on the far turn and flattened in the lane. BEST VIRGINIA rounded the first turn in the four path, picked up the chase nearing the seven sixteenths pole, came through the far turn about the five path and showed little in the lane. TRUST THE NUMBERS stalked from the three path the first turn, took a slim lead approaching the seven sixteenths pole and dueled at even terms from that point, but was met while between horses past the quarter pole and weakened in the lane. WISHING FOR SPRING saved ground on the first turn, gave chase nearing the three eighths pole but flattened stride at the rail on the far turn. CONNECTING FLIGHT rounded the first turn about the four path and loped around.
